00:00:15.040 --> 00:00:19.180
Potamia (Ποταμιά) is a village on the island of Thasos, Greece.

00:00:22.040 --> 00:00:26.060
It is built in the valley at the foot of Mount Ipsario,

00:00:39.620 --> 00:00:44.360
and surrounded to the south and east by pine and sweet chestnut forests.

00:01:45.720 --> 00:01:50.960
Its coastal annexe is the holiday resort of Skala Potamias.

00:02:00.600 --> 00:02:04.740
Potamia was the birthplace of the Greek-born American sculptor Polygnotos Vagis,

00:02:08.280 --> 00:02:12.320
and a museum dedicated to his work exists in the village.

00:04:05.620 --> 00:04:10.340
Etymologically, the name of the village

00:04:16.560 --> 00:04:21.500
is derived from the streams that run through it."

